cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with privacy-preserving publishing of spatiotemporal trajectory data, which involves data management, security, and privacy concerns. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm that generalizes the data, which involves machine learning and data mining techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper also mentions scaling up studies across research disciplines, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
